      "text": "L: I think so. That is, of course, it depends on what you mean by normative. But if, at the same time, one prescribes with the theory that others must accept it or fall into some zone of badness, of intemperance, of.... (I don't know how you want to classify it), then I think, first of all, that is not scientifically seen, because you would have to give the others the chance to do it better, from their preferences, and besides, you don't need that at all. And that's what I mean by the political or moral content of theory. If they claim that, they classify their opponents with it, and I want to avoid that. "
