      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "f7e3938844a09938",
      "text": "L: Yes, yes. Essentially you can include that via self-reference figures, I think. So that if you say society can only be described in society and writing must be an operation that society tolerates, that is, communication – then that's actually caught, I think. It's just that it's become circular, sort of. And it changes historically with the change of foci of attention that society itself generates or also with the help of the figures of theory that illuminate something and obscure something else."
